article.headline: Bradley 51, N. Iowa 48
article.story: ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Will Franklin hit an off-balance 3-pointer with 2.7 seconds left to lift Bradley to a 51-48 victory over Northern Iowa on Friday in the quarterfinals of the Missouri Valley Conference tournament. Franklin held for the final shot before driving toward the basket and almost turned the ball over. He regained control and took taking an awkward fall-away shot with Jared Josten closely guarding him for his second 3-pointer of the game. Bradley (21-11) plays No. 11 Southern Illinois on Saturday in the semifinals. Southern Illinois, the top seed, split with the Braves during the regular season with each teams winning at home. J.J. Tauai scored 16 and Franklin added 12 for Bradley, which lost twice to Northern Iowa in the regular season. Jeremy Crouch gave the Braves a 38-29 lead with 11:15 left before Northern Iowa (18-13) chipped away. Grant Stout, who had game-highs of 19 points and nine rebounds, gave the Panthers their first lead at 48-46 on a 3-pointer from the top of the key with just over two minutes left. Tauai tied the game about a minute later, scoring on a put-back after Eric Coleman blocked Tauai's first attempt. The Braves jumped out to an 18-4 lead in the first nine minutes of the game before enduring a six-minute scoring drought. The Panthers scored 12 unanswered points in that span and pulled to within 18-16 on Stout's 3-pointer with 5:38 left before halftime. Tauai answered 19 seconds later with a 3-pointer from the right corner and Bradley went on a 10-5 spurt to take a 28-21 lead at the break.
